Program: Outlook
Title: 11/03/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p006j7rq
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 12 Mar 2010
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world with Matthew Bannister. Julian Hendy We talk to the British film maker whose life was turned upside down when his father was randomly killed by a schizophrenic. We also hear from Professor Sheilagh Hodgins, head of Forensic Medicine at the Institute of Psychiatry at Kings College in London. Finding Love Online: Inter-racial Dating Jane O'Brien has been to meet a mixed race couple in Washington DC, who tell her about the prejudices they have faced. Karyn Langhorne Folan's book is called Don't Bring Home a White Boy. Show less